title: "ITU and Agriculture & Food Systems: A Single-Axiom View of Crops, Livestock, GMO/CRISPR, Precision Agriculture, Climate, Water, Food Security, and AI Agriculture — Pass-1 Extension Paper #11, Block D 3/5"
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Terada
    given-names: Munehiro
    affiliation: Roboken
    email: munehiro.terada@roboken2.com
abstract: >
  We apply the Information-Theoretic Unification (ITU) framework
  (Terada 2026, concept DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20109209; Tier 0 v3.0 at
  10.5281/zenodo.20200156) to agriculture and food systems. Tier 1
  paper #41, eleventh paper of Pass-1 extension, Block D 3/5 = 60%
  (after #39 Manufacturing and #40 Transportation). Introduces
  K_agri across 8 sub-states (crops, livestock, GMO, precision,
  climate, water, food, AI). ITU axiom delta S = delta <K> verified
  to machine precision in 11 contexts. 41-vertex ITU polytope.
  Theoretical position: Agriculture = K-state biological-anthropogenic
  energy/matter conversion. Food security = production x distribution
  efficiency. AI agriculture = K-state optimization across
  space-time-biology.
  Key results: BC 9,500 agricultural revolution (Fertile Crescent),
  BC 8,000 rice (Yangtze), BC 7,000 maize (Mexico), 1798 Malthus,
  1909 Haber-Bosch nitrogen fixation (Haber Nobel 1918, feeds 50%
  world population per Smil 2001).
  Crops: Mendel 1865 Brno, Shull hybrid corn 1908, US corn yield 30
  -> 180 bu/acre (6x in 90 yr), Borlaug Mexico 1944-1963 semi-dwarf
  wheat, IRRI Philippines 1960 founded, IR8 Miracle Rice 1966, India
  wheat 12.3 -> 49.9 Mt (1965-1990 4x), Borlaug Nobel Peace 1970
  ("saved a billion lives"), top crops 2024 maize 1.2 Gt + wheat
  800 Mt + rice 520 Mt + soy 400 Mt, Svalbard Vault 2008 (1.2M
  samples), Russia-Ukraine 30% wheat exports pre-war.
  Livestock: 1.6B cattle + 33B chickens + 780M pigs, meat 360 Mt
  (chicken 130 / pork 110 / beef 75), livestock 14% global GHG
  (FAO 2013), beef 15000 L water/kg vs chicken 4000, aquaculture
  88 Mt (China 65 #1 60%+), Beyond Meat 2009 + Impossible Foods
  2011, Beyond IPO 2019 $4B, Post Maastricht first cultivated burger
  2013 $330K, Singapore Eat Just GOOD Meat 2020.12 world's first,
  US FDA + USDA approve Upside + GOOD 2023.6, David Bennett
  xenotransplant 2022 (60 days GalSafe pig), plant-based $7.4B,
  GFI $14B raised 2010-2024, Perfect Day precision fermentation,
  Solar Foods Solein.
  GMO + CRISPR: Cohen-Boyer 1973 recombinant DNA, Flavr Savr 1994
  first commercial GMO food, 1996 RR soy + Bt corn/cotton, India
  Bt cotton 2002 (90% cotton 2014), Golden Rice (Potrykus-Beyer
  1999 GR1 / 2005 GR2, Time 2000 cover) Philippines commercial
  2021, Doudna-Charpentier Nobel Chemistry 2020, Sanatech CRISPR
  tomato Japan 2021 (world's first), US 72M ha GMO #1, global
  200M ha (12% arable), glyphosate IARC 2015 Group 2A, Bayer $11B
  Roundup settlement.
  Precision agriculture: 1992 USDA Yield Monitor, 2000 GPS civilian
  (Clinton), 2001 John Deere AutoTrac, 2013 DJI ag drones, 2024
  China 200K+ ag drones, DJI Agras T50 (50 kg payload, 21 ha/hour),
  John Deere See & Spray 2017 (herbicide -90%, Blue River
  Technology acquired 2017 $305M), Sentinel-2 ESA 2015 (10 m
  resolution, 5-day revisit), Despommier vertical farming concept
  2010 Columbia, Plenty $200M SoftBank 2018, AeroFarms bankruptcy
  2023, Netherlands Glass City 100 km^2 (#2 ag exporter),
  Lely Astronaut 50K+ robotic milkers.
  Climate + Water: IPCC AR6 yields per °C (wheat -1.9%, maize
  -1.5%, rice -0.9%, soy -2.7%), agriculture 70% global freshwater
  (FAO), India Punjab groundwater -1 m/yr, Ogallala 30% depleted,
  Blass drip irrigation 1959 + Netafim 1965 (water -30-50% vs
  flood), Israel 80% wastewater recycled, 24% global land degraded
  (UNCCD), 30 Gt soil lost annually, US no-till 100M acres,
  regenerative agriculture (Gabe Brown 5 principles), food loss +
  waste 1.3 Gt/yr = 33% (FAO), global organic $200B, carbon
  farming $15-50/t CO2.
  Food Security: 733M undernourished (9% world FAO 2024), 281M
  acute food insecurity (2023 worst), Sudan famine confirmed
  2024.8 (IPC 5), Gaza 50%+ acute, WFP Nobel Peace 2020 (David
  Beasley, $13B operations, 155M food assistance), Black Sea Grain
  Initiative 2022.7 (32 Mt grain) -> Russia withdraws 2023.7.
  AI agriculture: Climate Corp Monsanto 2013 $930M, Blue River
  John Deere 2017 $305M, Plantix 1M+ smallholder users, 2023-2024
  GPT-4 + LLM agriculture (multilingual advisory, disease
  diagnosis), AGRA 2006 Gates Africa.
  Ten falsifiable predictions (P_avg = 0.805; Strong/Medium/Weak =
  8/2/0) including AI advisory 100M+ smallholder farmers 2028
  (P=0.85), CRISPR crops 10+ commercial 2028 (P=0.85), autonomous
  tractors 50%+ major OEM 2028 (P=0.85), cultivated meat 5+
  countries approved 2028 (P=0.85), ag drones 1M+ globally 2027
  (P=0.85), VRA standard major US/EU farms 2027 (P=0.85), EU
  CRISPR regulation reform 2026 (P=0.80), climate-adapted seeds
  80%+ 2030 (P=0.75, Medium), Africa yield 2x smallholder 2030
  (P=0.55, Medium), SDG 2 Zero Hunger 2030 fails negative
  prediction (P=0.85). Block D 3/5 = 60%. Pass-1 extension 11/15 =
  73.3%. Pass-1 interpretive synthesis.
